  "prompt": "Why did Apple change its name from Apple Computers Incorporated to Apple Inc?\"?",
  "response": "Apple changed its name from Apple Computer, Inc. to Apple Inc. in January 2007 to reflect the company's broader focus beyond just personal computers. This name change came shortly after Apple introduced the iPhone at the Macworld Conference, signaling the company's expansion into other consumer electronics and digital devices like the iPod, iPhone, and later the iPad. The new name more accurately represented Apple's identity as a technology and consumer electronics company, rather than being limited to just computer manufacturing.",
